National Transportation Safety Board
Aviation Accident Final Report
Location: TEMPLE, TX
Accident Number: FTW82DA074
Date & Time: 03/01/1982, 1100 CST
Registration: N2395L
Aircraft: PIPER PA-38-112
Aircraft Damage: Substantial
Defining Event:
Injuries: 1 None
Flight Conducted Under: Part 91: General Aviation - Personal
 Analysis THE PILOT DECIDED TO PRACTICE TAKEOFFS AND LANDINGS ON RUNWAY 15 WITH THE WIND FROM 190 DEGREES AT 20 GUSTING 30 KTS.
DURING THE FIRST LANDING, THE AIRCRAFT TOUCHED DOWN, BOUNCED/BALLOONED, THEN TOUCHED DOWN HARD IN A NOSE DOWN ATTITUDE.
THE AIRCRAFT WAS SUBSTANTIALLY DAMAGED WHEN THE NOSE GEAR FAILED.
Probable Cause and Findings The National Transportation Safety Board determines the probable cause(s) of this accident to be: Findings Occurrence #1: HARD LANDING Phase of Operation: LANDING - FLARE/TOUCHDOWN Findings 1.
(F) WEATHER CONDITION - HIGH WIND 2.
(F) WEATHER CONDITION - CROSSWIND 3.
(F) WEATHER CONDITION - GUSTS 4.
(C) LEVEL OFF - IMPROPER - PILOT IN COMMAND 5.
(C) RECOVERY FROM BOUNCED LANDING - IMPROPER - PILOT IN COMMAND ---------- Occurrence #2: NOSE GEAR COLLAPSED Phase of Operation: LANDING - FLARE/TOUCHDOWN Findings 6.
(F) LANDING GEAR,NOSE GEAR - OVERLOAD Factual Information Pilot Information Certificate: Private Age: , Male Airplane Rating(s): Single-engine Land Seat Occupied: Unknown Other Aircraft Rating(s): Restraint Used: Instrument Rating(s): None Second Pilot Present: No Instructor Rating(s): None Toxicology Performed: Medical Certification: Class 3 Valid Medical--no waivers/lim.
: 1690 lbs Time Since Last Inspection: 80 Hours Engines: 1 Reciprocating Airframe Total Time: 856 Hours Engine Manufacturer: LYCOMING ELT: Installed, not activated Engine Model/Series: O-235-L2C Registered Owner: TEMPLE AVIATION INC.
